      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:153:1",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/153/5663",
      "text": [
        " \"إِذَا كَانَ أَبَوَاهُمَا اَللَّذَانِ زَوَّجَاهُمَا فَنَعَمْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5663 - Al-Nadr ibn Suwayd narrated from Al-Qasim ibn Sulayman, from Ubayd ibn Zurarah, who said: He asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a boy being married to a girl - do they inherit from one another?\nImam (as) said: \"If it was their parents who arranged their marriage, then yes, they do inherit from each other.\""
        ]
      }
    },
